## ðŸ’¡ **Week 5-6: Solution Validation & Business Model**

### **3.1 Solution Concept Testing**

#### **Concept Validation Framework:**
```
Solution Testing Methods:
â”œâ”€â”€ Landing Page Tests (conversion rates)
â”œâ”€â”€ Mockup Feedback Sessions
â”œâ”€â”€ Feature Priority Ranking
â”œâ”€â”€ Prototype Testing (Figma/InVision)
â”œâ”€â”€ A/B Test Concept Variations
â””â”€â”€ Pre-launch Sign-up Campaign
```

#### **Key Concepts to Test:**
1. **Hidden Gem Algorithm**: AI-powered discovery of lesser-known restaurants
2. **Community-Driven Reviews**: Verified, photo-required reviews
3. **Taste Profile Matching**: Personalized recommendations
4. **Social Discovery**: Friend-based recommendations
5. **Real-time Features**: Live wait times, specials, availability

### **3.2 Business Model Validation**

#### **Revenue Model Testing:**
```
Business Model Experiments:
â”œâ”€â”€ Freemium Model (free vs premium features)
â”œâ”€â”€ Restaurant Partnership Fees
â”œâ”€â”€ Advertising Revenue (restaurant promotions)
â”œâ”€â”€ Commission on Reservations/Orders
â”œâ”€â”€ Subscription Tiers (individual vs business)
â””â”€â”€ Data Licensing (anonymized insights)
```

#### **Pricing Research:**
- **Survey-based pricing**: Van Westendorp Price Sensitivity Meter
- **Competitive pricing analysis**: What users currently pay
- **Value-based pricing**: Price based on problem severity
- **A/B pricing tests**: Different price points for same value

### **3.3 Go-to-Market Strategy Development**

#### **Customer Acquisition Research:**
```
Channel Validation:
â”œâ”€â”€ Social Media Marketing (Instagram, TikTok food content)
â”œâ”€â”€ SEO/Content Marketing (food blogs, local guides)
â”œâ”€â”€ Partnership Channels (food influencers, local businesses)
â”œâ”€â”€ App Store Optimization
â”œâ”€â”€ Referral Programs
â”œâ”€â”€ Local Marketing (events, partnerships)
â””â”€â”€ Paid Advertising (Google, Facebook, Instagram)
```

